# ===========================
# E-commerce Platform Spec
# ===========================

# --- Core Entities ---

ent1 A User is a person who has registered an account with an email and password
ent2 A Product is an item available for purchase with a name, description, price, and inventory count
ent3 A Cart is a temporary collection of products associated with a single user
ent4 An Order is a confirmed purchase created from a cart with a total, status, and timestamp
ent5 A Review is a rating and comment left by a user on a product they have purchased
ent6 A Category is a named grouping used to organize products
ent7 A Seller is a user who has been granted permission to list and manage products

# --- Authentication ---

auth1 A visitor can create an account by providing an email, display name, and password
auth2 Given {ent1} a user can log in with their email and password
auth3@asm A logged-in user receives a session token that expires after 24 hours of inactivity
auth4 Given {auth3} any request with an expired token must redirect to the login page
auth5 A user can request a password reset link sent to their registered email
auth6@asm Given {auth5} the reset link expires after 1 hour and can only be used once
auth7 Given {ent7} a seller must complete identity verification before listing products

# --- Product Catalog ---

cat1 Given {ent2} and {ent6} every product must belong to at least one category
cat2 A product page displays its name, description, price, images, average rating, and reviews
cat3@asm Given {cat2} and {ent5} reviews are sorted by most recent by default
cat4 Products can be searched by name or description using full-text search
cat5 Given {cat4} search results are ranked by relevance and can be filtered by category and price range
cat6 Given {ent2} if a product inventory count reaches zero it is shown as out of stock
cat7 Given {cat6} an out of stock product cannot be added to a cart
cat8 Given {ent7} a seller can create, edit, and archive their own products but not products from other sellers

# --- Shopping Cart ---

cart1 Given {ent1} and {ent3} a logged-in user has exactly one active cart at any time
cart2 Given {ent2} and {cart1} a user can add a product to their cart with a specified quantity
cart3 Given {cart2} and {ent2} the requested quantity cannot exceed the product inventory count
cart4 Given {cart1} the cart displays each item with its name, unit price, quantity, and line total
cart5 Given {cart4} the cart displays a subtotal that is the sum of all line totals
cart6 Given {cart2} a user can update the quantity of an item or remove it from the cart
cart7@asm Given {cart1} the cart persists across sessions so a user can return and find their items

# --- Checkout & Orders ---

ord1 Given {cart5} a user can proceed to checkout if their cart has at least one item
ord2 Given {ord1} checkout requires a shipping address and a payment method
ord3 Given {ord2} the system validates the payment method before creating the order
ord4 Given {ord3} and {ent4} a successful payment creates an order with status pending
ord5 Given {ord4} and {ent2} creating an order decrements the inventory count of each purchased product
ord6 Given {ord4} the user receives an order confirmation email with a summary and order number
ord7 Given {ent4} an order progresses through statuses pending then shipped then delivered
ord8 Given {ord7} the user can view the current status and estimated delivery date on the order page
ord9@rsk Given {ord7} a user can cancel an order only while its status is pending
ord10@unk Given {ord9} it is unclear whether cancellation should trigger an immediate refund or a refund request
ord11@unk Given {ord5} the behavior when two users checkout the last item simultaneously is undefined

# --- Reviews ---

rev1 Given {ent1} and {ent5} and {ent4} a user can only review a product they have purchased
rev2 Given {rev1} a review includes a rating from 1 to 5 and an optional text comment
rev3 Given {rev1} a user can submit at most one review per product
rev4 Given {rev3} a user can edit or delete their own review at any time
rev5 Given {ent5} and {cat2} the average rating displayed on the product page updates when reviews change
rev6@rsk Given {rev4} allowing review deletion could enable sellers to pressure users into removing negative reviews
rev7@unk Given {rev2} it is undecided whether reviews should support image attachments

# --- Seller Dashboard ---

sell1 Given {ent7} a seller can view a dashboard showing all their listed products and sales
sell2 Given {sell1} and {ent4} the dashboard shows total revenue and number of orders per product
sell3 Given {sell1} a seller can see which products are low in stock defined as inventory below 10
sell4 Given {sell3} the system sends an email alert to the seller when a product inventory drops below 5
sell5@asm Given {sell3} the low stock threshold of 10 is suitable for all product types

# --- Access Control ---

ac1 Given {ent1} an unauthenticated visitor can browse products and categories but cannot add to cart
ac2 Given {auth2} and {cart2} only an authenticated user can add items to a cart or place an order
ac3 Given {ent7} and {cat8} a seller can only manage their own products
ac4 An admin can suspend any user account or remove any product or review
ac5 Given {ac4} suspended users cannot log in and see a message explaining their suspension
ac6@rsk Given {ac4} there is no audit trail for admin actions which could lead to abuse

# --- Performance & Reliability ---

perf1@asm Given {cat4} search results must return within 200 milliseconds for up to 100000 products
perf2@asm Given {ord3} payment processing must complete or timeout within 10 seconds
perf3 Given {perf2} if payment times out the order is not created and the user is shown an error
perf4 Given {cart7} cart data must be durable across server restarts using persistent storage
perf5@asm The system must support 1000 concurrent authenticated users without degradation
perf6@unk Given {perf5} it is unknown whether 1000 concurrent users is a realistic peak load estimate
